    ///All Securities
    ///
    ///Returns a list of all securities available. Delisted securities
    /// included.
    ///
    ///Sends a `GET` request to `/securities`
    ///
    ///Arguments:
    /// - `active`: When true, return securities that are active. When false,
    ///   return securities that are not active. A security is considered active
    ///   if it has traded or has had a corporate action in the past 30 days,
    ///   and has not been merged into another security (such as due to ticker
    ///   changes or corporate restructurings).
    /// - `cik`: Return securities belonging to the company with the given
    ///   Central Index Key (CIK).
    /// - `code`: Return securities classified with the given code (<a href="https://docs.intrinio.com/documentation/security_codes" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `composite_figi`: Return securities with the given Country Composite FIGI (<a href="https://www.openfigi.com/about" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `composite_mic`: Return securities classified under the composite
    ///   exchange with the given Market Identification Code (MIC). A composite
    ///   exchange may or may not be a real exchange.  For example, the USCOMP
    ///   exchange (our only composite exchange to date) is a combination of
    ///   exchanges with the following MICs: ARCX, XASE, XPOR, FINR, XCIS, XNAS,
    ///   XNYS, BATS.  This composite grouping is done for user convenience.  At
    ///   this time, all US securities are classified under the composite
    ///   exchange with MIC USCOMP.  To query for specific US exchanges, use the
    ///   exchange_mic parameter below.
    ///
    /// - `currency`: Return securities traded in the given 3-digit ISO 4217 currency code (<a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/ISO_4217" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `delisted`: When true, return securities that have been delisted from
    ///   their exchange. Note that there may be a newer security for the same
    ///   company that has been relisted on a differente exchange. When false,
    ///   return securities that have not been delisted.
    /// - `exchange_mic`: The MIC code of the exchange where the security is
    ///   actually traded.
    /// - `figi`: Return securities with the given Exchange Level FIGI (<a href="https://www.openfigi.com/about" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `figi_unique_id`: Return securities with the given FIGI Unique ID (<a href="https://www.openfigi.com/about" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `include_non_figi`: When true, include securities that do not have a
    ///   FIGI. By default, this is false. If this parameter is not specified,
    ///   only securities with a FIGI are returned.
    /// - `name`: Return securities with the given text in their name (not case
    ///   sensitive).
    /// - `next_page`: Gets the next page of data from a previous API call
    /// - `page_size`: The number of results to return
    /// - `primary_listing`: If true, the Security is the primary issue for the
    ///   company, otherwise it is a secondary issue on a secondary stock
    ///   exchange.  Returns both if omitted.
    /// - `share_class_figi`: Return securities with the given Global Share Class FIGI (<a href="https://www.openfigi.com/about" target="_blank">reference</a>).
    /// - `stock_prices_after`: Return securities with end-of-day stock prices
    ///   on or after this date.
    /// - `stock_prices_before`: Return securities with end-of-day stock prices
    ///   on or before this date.
    /// - `ticker`: Return securities traded with the given ticker. Note that
